    "text": "In Senegal, SMEs account for more than 93% of the productive fabric but face severe constraints in accessing bank financing.",
    "topic": "SME financing constraints in Senegal"
  },
  {
    "text": "Credit interentreprise is the primary source of external financing for Senegalese SMEs, representing 65% of the GDP in 2023, equivalent to 12,106 billion CFA francs.",
    "topic": "Credit interentreprise in Senegal"
  },
  {
    "text": "The study uses a dynamic panel approach on data spanning from 1999 to 2023 to analyze determinants of interenterprise credit in Senegal.",
    "topic": "Dynamic panel analysis of credit determinants"
  },
  {
    "text": "Data for the analysis were sourced from the sectoral economic and financial database (BDEF) of the National Statistics and Demography Agency.",
    "topic": "Data source for the study"
  },
  {
    "text": "The period covered by the study is from 1999 to 2023.",
    "topic": "Study period"
  }
]
